Returns if self contains data members capable of producing an overall valid MazeTokenizerModular.

Some _TokenizerElement instances may be created which are not useful despite obeying data member type hints. is_valid allows for more precise detection of invalid _TokenizerElements beyond type hinting alone. If type hints are sufficient to constrain the possible instances of some subclass, then this method may simply return True for that subclass.

Types of Invalidity

In nontrivial implementations of this method, each conditional clause should contain a comment classifying the reason for invalidity and one of the types below. Invalidity types, in ascending order of invalidity:

  • Uninteresting: These tokenizers might be used to train functional models, but the schemes are not interesting to study. E.g., _TokenizerElements which are strictly worse than some alternative.
  • Duplicate: These tokenizers have identical tokenization behavior as some other valid tokenizers.
  • Untrainable: Training functional models using these tokenizers would be (nearly) impossible.
  • Erroneous: These tokenizers might raise exceptions during use.

Development

is_invalid is implemented to always return True in some abstract classes where all currently possible subclass instances are valid. When adding new subclasses or data members, the developer should check if any such blanket statement of validity still holds and update it as neccesary.

Nesting

In general, when implementing this method, there is no need to recursively call is_valid on nested _TokenizerElements contained in the class. In other words, failures of is_valid need not bubble up to the top of the nested _TokenizerElement tree. MazeTokenizerModular.is_valid calls is_valid on each of its _TokenizerElements individually, so failure at any level will be detected.

Types of Invalidity

If it's judged to be useful, the types of invalidity could be implemented with an Enum or similar rather than only living in comments. This could be used to create more or less stringent filters on the valid _TokenizerElement instances.

def serialize(self) -> dict[str, typing.Any]:
View on GitHub 
714        def serialize(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
715            result: dict[str, Any] = {
716                _FORMAT_KEY: f"{self.__class__.__name__}(SerializableDataclass)"
717            }
718            # for each field in the class
719            for field in dataclasses.fields(self):  # type: ignore[arg-type]
720                # need it to be our special SerializableField
721                if not isinstance(field, SerializableField):
722                    raise NotSerializableFieldException(
723                        f"Field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__} is not a `SerializableField`, "
724                        f"but a {type(field)} "
725                        "this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!"
726                    )
727
728                # try to save it
729                if field.serialize:
730                    try:
731                        # get the val
732                        value = getattr(self, field.name)
733                        # if it is a serializable dataclass, serialize it
734                        if isinstance(value, SerializableDataclass):
735                            value = value.serialize()
736                        # if the value has a serialization function, use that
737                        if hasattr(value, "serialize") and callable(value.serialize):
738                            value = value.serialize()
739                        # if the field has a serialization function, use that
740                        # it would be nice to be able to override a class's `.serialize()`, but that could lead to some inconsistencies!
741                        elif field.serialization_fn:
742                            value = field.serialization_fn(value)
743
744                        # store the value in the result
745                        result[field.name] = value
746                    except Exception as e:
747                        raise FieldSerializationError(
748                            "\n".join(
749                                [
750                                    f"Error serializing field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}",
751                                    f"{field = }",
752                                    f"{value = }",
753                                    f"{self = }",
754                                ]
755                            )
756                        ) from e
757
758            # store each property if we can get it
759            for prop in self._properties_to_serialize:
760                if hasattr(cls, prop):
761                    value = getattr(self, prop)
762                    result[prop] = value
763                else:
764                    raise AttributeError(
765                        f"Cannot serialize property '{prop}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}"
766                        + f"but it is in {self._properties_to_serialize = }"
767                        + f"\n{self = }"
768                    )
769
770            return result

777        @classmethod  # type: ignore[misc]
778        def load(cls, data: dict[str, Any] | T) -> Type[T]:
779            # HACK: this is kind of ugly, but it fixes a lot of issues for when we do recursive loading with ZANJ
780            if isinstance(data, cls):
781                return data
782
783            assert isinstance(
784                data, typing.Mapping
785            ), f"When loading {cls.__name__ = } expected a Mapping, but got {type(data) = }:\n{data = }"
786
787            cls_type_hints: dict[str, Any] = get_cls_type_hints(cls)
788
789            # initialize dict for keeping what we will pass to the constructor
790            ctor_kwargs: dict[str, Any] = dict()
791
792            # iterate over the fields of the class
793            for field in dataclasses.fields(cls):
794                # check if the field is a SerializableField
795                assert isinstance(
796                    field, SerializableField
797                ), f"Field '{field.name}' on class {cls.__name__} is not a SerializableField, but a {type(field)}. this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!\nhttps://github.com/mivanit/muutils/issues/new"
798
799                # check if the field is in the data and if it should be initialized
800                if (field.name in data) and field.init:
801                    # get the value, we will be processing it
802                    value: Any = data[field.name]
803
804                    # get the type hint for the field
805                    field_type_hint: Any = cls_type_hints.get(field.name, None)
806
807                    # we rely on the init of `SerializableField` to check that only one of `loading_fn` and `deserialize_fn` is set
808                    if field.deserialize_fn:
809                        # if it has a deserialization function, use that
810                        value = field.deserialize_fn(value)
811                    elif field.loading_fn:
812                        # if it has a loading function, use that
813                        value = field.loading_fn(data)
814                    elif (
815                        field_type_hint is not None
816                        and hasattr(field_type_hint, "load")
817                        and callable(field_type_hint.load)
818                    ):
819                        # if no loading function but has a type hint with a load method, use that
820                        if isinstance(value, dict):
821                            value = field_type_hint.load(value)
822                        else:
823                            raise FieldLoadingError(
824                                f"Cannot load value into {field_type_hint}, expected {type(value) = } to be a dict\n{value = }"
825                            )
826                    else:
827                        # assume no loading needs to happen, keep `value` as-is
828                        pass
829
830                    # store the value in the constructor kwargs
831                    ctor_kwargs[field.name] = value
832
833            # create a new instance of the class with the constructor kwargs
834            output: cls = cls(**ctor_kwargs)
835
836            # validate the types of the fields if needed
837            if on_typecheck_mismatch != ErrorMode.IGNORE:
838                fields_valid: dict[str, bool] = (
839                    SerializableDataclass__validate_fields_types__dict(
840                        output,
841                        on_typecheck_error=on_typecheck_error,
842                    )
843                )
844
845                # if there are any fields that are not valid, raise an error
846                if not all(fields_valid.values()):
847                    msg: str = (
848                        f"Type mismatch in fields of {cls.__name__}:\n"
849                        + "\n".join(
850                            [
851                                f"{k}:\texpected {cls_type_hints[k] = }, but got value {getattr(output, k) = }, {type(getattr(output, k)) = }"
852                                for k, v in fields_valid.items()
853                                if not v
854                            ]
855                        )
856                    )
857
858                    on_typecheck_mismatch.process(
859                        msg, except_cls=FieldTypeMismatchError
860                    )
861
862            # return the new instance
863            return output

164@serializable_dataclass(
165	properties_to_serialize=_MAZETOKENIZER_PROPERTIES_TO_SERIALIZE,

168class MazeTokenizer(SerializableDataclass):
169	"""LEGACY Tokenizer for mazes
170
171	> [!CAUTION]
172	> `MazeTokenizerModular` is the new standard for tokenization. This class is no longer recommended
173	> for use, but will remain for compatibility with existing code.
174
175	# Parameters:
176	- `tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode`
177		mode of tokenization. required.
178	- `max_grid_size: int | None`
179		maximum grid size. required for actually turning text tokens to numerical tokens, but not for moving between coordinates/mazes and text
180
181	# Properties
182	- `name: str`
183		auto-generated name of the tokenizer from mode and size
184
185	## Conditional Properties
186
187	- `node_strings_map: Mapping[CoordTup, str]`
188		map from node to string. This returns a `muutils.kappa.Kappa` object which you can use like a dictionary. returns `None` if not a `UT` mode
189
190	these all return `None` if `max_grid_size` is `None`.
191	Prepend `_` to the name to get a guaranteed type, and cause an exception if `max_grid_size` is `None`
192
193	- `token_arr: list[str]`
194		list of tokens, in order of their indices in the vocabulary
195	- `tokenizer_map: Mapping[str, int]`
196		map from token to index
197	- `vocab_size: int`
198		size of the vocabulary
199	- `padding_token_index: int`
200		index of the padding token
201
202	# Methods
203	- `coords_to_strings(coords: list[CoordTup]) -> list[str]`
204		convert a list of coordinates to a list of tokens. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
205	- `strings_to_coords(strings: list[str]) -> list[CoordTup]`
206		convert a list of tokens to a list of coordinates. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
207
208	"""
209

214		default=TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,

216		loading_fn=lambda x: TokenizationMode[x["tokenization_mode"]],
217	)

224	@property
225	def name(self) -> str:
226		"""auto-generated name of the tokenizer from mode and size"""
227		max_grid_size_str: str = (
228			f"-g{self.max_grid_size}" if self.max_grid_size is not None else ""
229		)
230		return f"maze_tokenizer-{self.tokenization_mode.value}{max_grid_size_str}"
231
232	@cached_property
233	def _node_strings_map(self) -> Mapping[CoordTup, list[str]]:
234		"""map a coordinate to a token"""
235		if self.tokenization_mode in (
236			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
237			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
238		):
239			return Kappa(_coord_to_strings_UT)
240		elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
241			return Kappa(_coord_to_strings_indexed)
242		else:
243			err_msg: str = f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}, expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}"
244			raise ValueError(err_msg)
245
246	@cached_property
247	def node_strings_map(self) -> Mapping[CoordTup, list[str]] | None:
248		"""map a coordinate to a token"""
249		if self.tokenization_mode in (
250			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
251			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
252		):
253			return None
254		else:
255			return self._node_strings_map
256
257	# conditional properties (on max_grid_size existing)
258	# ------------------------------------------------------------
259
260	@cached_property
261	def _token_arr(self) -> list[str]:
262		"""map from index to token"""
263		if self.max_grid_size is None:
264			err_msg: str = f"max_grid_size must be specified to use token_arr property: {self.max_grid_size = }"
265			raise ValueError(err_msg)
266
267		output: list[str] = list(SPECIAL_TOKENS.values())
268
269		if self.tokenization_mode in (
270			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
271			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
272		):
273			output.extend(
274				[
275					self._node_strings_map[coord][0]
276					for coord in _NDINDEX_FUNC_MAP[self.tokenization_mode](
277						self.max_grid_size,
278					)
279				],
280			)
281		elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
282			# TODO: this is hacky, but we don't want to modify the original SPECIAL_TOKENS since that will break old models
283			output.extend(
284				[
285					"(",
286					",",
287					")",  # new special chars
288					*map(str, range(self.max_grid_size)),  # numbers
289				],
290			)
291		else:
292			err_msg: str = (
293				f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}, expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}",
294			)
295			raise ValueError(err_msg)
296
297		return output

299	@cached_property

301		"get the token array if the max_grid_size is specified"
302		if self.max_grid_size is None:
303			return None

306	@cached_property

308		"""map from token to index"""

315			return None

325		if self.max_grid_size is None:
326			return None
327		return self._vocab_size

336		"get the number of tokens if the max_grid_size is specified"
337		if self.max_grid_size is None:
338			return None
339		return self._n_tokens
340
341	@cached_property
342	def _padding_token_index(self) -> int:
343		return self.tokenizer_map[SPECIAL_TOKENS.PADDING]
344
345	@cached_property
346	def padding_token_index(self) -> int | None:
347		"get the index of the padding token if it exists"
348		if self.max_grid_size is None:
349			return None
350		return self._padding_token_index

355	@overload

357		self,
358		coords: list[str | CoordTup],
359		when_noncoord: Literal["include", "skip"] = "skip",
360	) -> list[str]: ...
361	@overload
362	def coords_to_strings(
363		self,
364		coords: list[CoordTup],
365		when_noncoord: Literal["error"] = "error",
366	) -> list[str]: ...
367	def coords_to_strings(
368		self,
369		coords: list[CoordTup],
370		when_noncoord: WhenMissing = "skip",
371	) -> list[str]:
372		"""map a list of coordinate tuples (and maybe other tokens) to strings
373
374		wraps `maze_dataset.token_utils.coords_to_strings` with either
375		`_coord_to_strings_UT` or `_coord_to_strings_indexed` depending on the tokenization mode
376		"""
377		if self.tokenization_mode in (
378			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
379			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
380		):
381			return coords_to_strings(
382				coords=coords,
383				coord_to_strings_func=_coord_to_strings_UT,
384				when_noncoord=when_noncoord,
385			)
386		elif self.tokenization_mode == TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed:
387			return coords_to_strings(
388				coords=coords,
389				coord_to_strings_func=_coord_to_strings_indexed,
390				when_noncoord=when_noncoord,
391			)
392		else:
393			err_msg: str = f"Invalid tokenization mode {self.tokenization_mode}, expected one of {TokenizationMode.__members__}"
394			raise ValueError(err_msg)
395
396	@overload
397	def strings_to_coords(
398		cls,  # noqa: N805
399		text: str | list[str],
400		when_noncoord: Literal["skip"] = "skip",
401	) -> list[CoordTup]: ...
402	@overload
403	def strings_to_coords(
404		cls,  # noqa: N805
405		text: str | list[str],
406		when_noncoord: Literal["error"] = "error",
407	) -> list[CoordTup]: ...
408	@overload
409	def strings_to_coords(
410		cls,  # noqa: N805
411		text: str | list[str],
412		when_noncoord: Literal["include"] = "include",
413	) -> list[str | CoordTup]: ...
414	@classmethod
415	def strings_to_coords(
416		cls,
417		text: str | list[str],
418		when_noncoord: WhenMissing = "skip",
419	) -> list[str | CoordTup]:
420		"wrapper for `maze_dataset.token_utils.strings_to_coords`"
421		return strings_to_coords(text=text, when_noncoord=when_noncoord)
422
423	def encode(self, text: str | list[str]) -> list[int]:
424		"""encode a string or list of strings into a list of tokens"""
425		try:
426			if isinstance(text, str):
427				text = text.split()
428			return [self.tokenizer_map[token] for token in text]
429		except KeyError as e:
430			err_msg: str = (
431				f"Token {e} not found in vocabulary of {self}:\n{self.token_arr}"
432			)
433			raise TokenError(err_msg) from e
434
435	def decode(
436		self,
437		tokens: Sequence[int],
438		joined_tokens: bool = False,
439	) -> list[str] | str:
440		"""decode a list of tokens into a string or list of strings"""
441		try:
442			output: list[str] = [self.token_arr[token] for token in tokens]
443		except IndexError as e:
444			err_msg: str = (
445				f"Token index '{e}' not found in vocabulary of length {self.vocab_size}"
446			)
447			raise TokenError(err_msg) from e
448		if joined_tokens:
449			return " ".join(output)
450		else:
451			return output
452
453	# UT-only coordinate stuff
454	# ============================================================
455
456	@cached_property
457	def coordinate_tokens_coords(self) -> dict[CoordTup, int]:
458		"map of coordiante tuples to their token ids, only valid for UT"
459		# print(f"{self.tokenization_mode = }")
460		if not self.is_UT():
461			err_msg: str = f"coordinate_tokens_coords is only valid for UT tokenization modes, got {self.tokenization_mode = }"
462			raise ValueError(err_msg)
463
464		if self.max_grid_size is None:
465			err_msg: str = f"max_grid_size must be specified to use coordinate_tokens: {self.max_grid_size = }"
466			raise ValueError(err_msg)
467
468		raw_converted: list[CoordTup | str] = self.strings_to_coords(
469			self.token_arr,
470			when_noncoord="include",
471		)
472
473		# filter out non-coordinates
474		return {
475			coord: i
476			for i, coord in enumerate(raw_converted)
477			if not isinstance(coord, str)
478		}
479
480	@cached_property
481	def coordinate_tokens_ids(self) -> dict[str, int]:
482		"map of coordinate tokens to their token ids, only valid for UT"
483		# checks performed in call
484		output: dict[str, int] = dict()
485
486		for coord, index in self.coordinate_tokens_coords.items():
487			_for_key: list[str] = self.coords_to_strings([coord])
488			assert len(_for_key) == 1
489			output[_for_key[0]] = index
490
491		return output
492
493	# other
494	# ============================================================
495
496	def summary(self) -> dict:
497		"""returns a summary of the tokenization mode"""
498		return {
499			"tokenization_mode": self.tokenization_mode.value,
500			"max_grid_size": self.max_grid_size,
501			"vocab_size": self.vocab_size,
502		}
503
504	def is_AOTP(self) -> bool:
505		"""returns true if a tokenization mode is Adjacency list, Origin, Target, Path"""
506		return self.tokenization_mode in (
507			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_rasterized,
508			TokenizationMode.AOTP_UT_uniform,
509			TokenizationMode.AOTP_CTT_indexed,
510		)
511
512	def is_UT(self) -> bool:
513		"returns true if a tokenization mode is a UT mode: UT = Unique Token (for each coordinate)"
514		return is_UT(self.tokenization_mode)
515
516	def clear_cache(self) -> None:
517		"""clears all cached properties"""
518		# delete the properties only if they exist
519		for name, prop in self.__class__.__dict__.items():
520			if isinstance(prop, cached_property):
521				# if the property exists, delete it
522				try:  # noqa: SIM105
523					delattr(self, name)
524				except AttributeError:
525					pass

LEGACY Tokenizer for mazes

Caution

MazeTokenizerModular is the new standard for tokenization. This class is no longer recommended for use, but will remain for compatibility with existing code.

Parameters:

  • tokenization_mode: TokenizationMode mode of tokenization. required.
  • max_grid_size: int | None maximum grid size. required for actually turning text tokens to numerical tokens, but not for moving between coordinates/mazes and text

Properties

  • name: str auto-generated name of the tokenizer from mode and size

Conditional Properties

  • node_strings_map: Mapping[CoordTup, str] map from node to string. This returns a muutils.kappa.Kappa object which you can use like a dictionary. returns None if not a UT mode

these all return None if max_grid_size is None. Prepend _ to the name to get a guaranteed type, and cause an exception if max_grid_size is None

  • token_arr: list[str] list of tokens, in order of their indices in the vocabulary
  • tokenizer_map: Mapping[str, int] map from token to index
  • vocab_size: int size of the vocabulary
  • padding_token_index: int index of the padding token

Methods

  • coords_to_strings(coords: list[CoordTup]) -> list[str] convert a list of coordinates to a list of tokens. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates
  • strings_to_coords(strings: list[str]) -> list[CoordTup] convert a list of tokens to a list of coordinates. Optionally except, skip, or ignore non-coordinates

def serialize(self) -> dict[str, typing.Any]:
View on GitHub 
714        def serialize(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
715            result: dict[str, Any] = {
716                _FORMAT_KEY: f"{self.__class__.__name__}(SerializableDataclass)"
717            }
718            # for each field in the class
719            for field in dataclasses.fields(self):  # type: ignore[arg-type]
720                # need it to be our special SerializableField
721                if not isinstance(field, SerializableField):
722                    raise NotSerializableFieldException(
723                        f"Field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__} is not a `SerializableField`, "
724                        f"but a {type(field)} "
725                        "this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!"
726                    )
727
728                # try to save it
729                if field.serialize:
730                    try:
731                        # get the val
732                        value = getattr(self, field.name)
733                        # if it is a serializable dataclass, serialize it
734                        if isinstance(value, SerializableDataclass):
735                            value = value.serialize()
736                        # if the value has a serialization function, use that
737                        if hasattr(value, "serialize") and callable(value.serialize):
738                            value = value.serialize()
739                        # if the field has a serialization function, use that
740                        # it would be nice to be able to override a class's `.serialize()`, but that could lead to some inconsistencies!
741                        elif field.serialization_fn:
742                            value = field.serialization_fn(value)
743
744                        # store the value in the result
745                        result[field.name] = value
746                    except Exception as e:
747                        raise FieldSerializationError(
748                            "\n".join(
749                                [
750                                    f"Error serializing field '{field.name}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}",
751                                    f"{field = }",
752                                    f"{value = }",
753                                    f"{self = }",
754                                ]
755                            )
756                        ) from e
757
758            # store each property if we can get it
759            for prop in self._properties_to_serialize:
760                if hasattr(cls, prop):
761                    value = getattr(self, prop)
762                    result[prop] = value
763                else:
764                    raise AttributeError(
765                        f"Cannot serialize property '{prop}' on class {self.__class__.__module__}.{self.__class__.__name__}"
766                        + f"but it is in {self._properties_to_serialize = }"
767                        + f"\n{self = }"
768                    )
769
770            return result

returns the class as a dict, implemented by using @serializable_dataclass decorator

@classmethod
def load(cls, data: Union[dict[str, Any], ~T]) -> Type[~T]:
View on GitHub 
777        @classmethod  # type: ignore[misc]
778        def load(cls, data: dict[str, Any] | T) -> Type[T]:
779            # HACK: this is kind of ugly, but it fixes a lot of issues for when we do recursive loading with ZANJ
780            if isinstance(data, cls):
781                return data
782
783            assert isinstance(
784                data, typing.Mapping
785            ), f"When loading {cls.__name__ = } expected a Mapping, but got {type(data) = }:\n{data = }"
786
787            cls_type_hints: dict[str, Any] = get_cls_type_hints(cls)
788
789            # initialize dict for keeping what we will pass to the constructor
790            ctor_kwargs: dict[str, Any] = dict()
791
792            # iterate over the fields of the class
793            for field in dataclasses.fields(cls):
794                # check if the field is a SerializableField
795                assert isinstance(
796                    field, SerializableField
797                ), f"Field '{field.name}' on class {cls.__name__} is not a SerializableField, but a {type(field)}. this state should be inaccessible, please report this bug!\nhttps://github.com/mivanit/muutils/issues/new"
798
799                # check if the field is in the data and if it should be initialized
800                if (field.name in data) and field.init:
801                    # get the value, we will be processing it
802                    value: Any = data[field.name]
803
804                    # get the type hint for the field
805                    field_type_hint: Any = cls_type_hints.get(field.name, None)
806
807                    # we rely on the init of `SerializableField` to check that only one of `loading_fn` and `deserialize_fn` is set
808                    if field.deserialize_fn:
809                        # if it has a deserialization function, use that
810                        value = field.deserialize_fn(value)
811                    elif field.loading_fn:
812                        # if it has a loading function, use that
813                        value = field.loading_fn(data)
814                    elif (
815                        field_type_hint is not None
816                        and hasattr(field_type_hint, "load")
817                        and callable(field_type_hint.load)
818                    ):
819                        # if no loading function but has a type hint with a load method, use that
820                        if isinstance(value, dict):
821                            value = field_type_hint.load(value)
822                        else:
823                            raise FieldLoadingError(
824                                f"Cannot load value into {field_type_hint}, expected {type(value) = } to be a dict\n{value = }"
825                            )
826                    else:
827                        # assume no loading needs to happen, keep `value` as-is
828                        pass
829
830                    # store the value in the constructor kwargs
831                    ctor_kwargs[field.name] = value
832
833            # create a new instance of the class with the constructor kwargs
834            output: cls = cls(**ctor_kwargs)
835
836            # validate the types of the fields if needed
837            if on_typecheck_mismatch != ErrorMode.IGNORE:
838                fields_valid: dict[str, bool] = (
839                    SerializableDataclass__validate_fields_types__dict(
840                        output,
841                        on_typecheck_error=on_typecheck_error,
842                    )
843                )
844
845                # if there are any fields that are not valid, raise an error
846                if not all(fields_valid.values()):
847                    msg: str = (
848                        f"Type mismatch in fields of {cls.__name__}:\n"
849                        + "\n".join(
850                            [
851                                f"{k}:\texpected {cls_type_hints[k] = }, but got value {getattr(output, k) = }, {type(getattr(output, k)) = }"
852                                for k, v in fields_valid.items()
853                                if not v
854                            ]
855                        )
856                    )
857
858                    on_typecheck_mismatch.process(
859                        msg, except_cls=FieldTypeMismatchError
860                    )
861
862            # return the new instance
863            return output

takes in an appropriately structured dict and returns an instance of the class, implemented by using @serializable_dataclass decorator
